      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ANDY WIN (5) finished third first-up from a spell over 2200m at Hamilton when he did his best work late. He's a second-up winner with more to offer. Maps well and will be hard to beat with the extra fitness. COUSINS DAY (3) led and missed a whisker in the same contest. The gate is awkward today, but has the early speed to manage and is sure to go close. ADJUDICATE (1) came home strongly to score by a long neck over 2000m at Warracknabeal. Had the blinkers back on and enjoyed the step-up in trip. Among the best chances again. MANGIONE (4) led and just missed in the same contest. Uses the rail and he's sure to give a big sight. COSMOS FACTORY (6) resumes and is likely headed to the jumps. Regardless, he may be the next best.",
